194-192, 190 and 189 South Street, north side, west from Oliver Street, to and including James Slip, showing (extreme right), the South Street high pressure pumping station of the Fire Department.  Contiguous to it is Abeel Bros. iron and steel shops.
September 7, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A portion of the same, showing only No. 190, the Abeel Bros. iron and steel shops.
May 3, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
A detail of view No. 1, showing the store front of No. 189, and the variety of marine articles sold there.  No. 189 also bears Nos. 16-20 James Slip and is at the N.E. corner.
March 19, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
